olive oil
1 packet chicken breast
½ block Parmesan cheese
2 unit onion
1 bag cos lettuce
2 unit tomato
2 unit carrot
1 tub mayonnaise
1 tub Dijon mustard
1 sachet Italian Herbs
4 tsp plain flour
½ tsp salt
1 tbs water (for the dressing)
1 tbs water (for the onion)
2.5 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tbs brown sugar
12 unit Mini Flour Tortillas
3 clove garlic

Thinly slice the red onion. Finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). Shred the cos lettuce. Thinly slice the tomato into half-moons. Thinly slice the carrot into batons. Grate the Parmesan cheese (see ingredients list). Slice the chicken breast into 1cm strips.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a medium frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes. Add the balsamic vinegar, water (for the onion) and brown sugar and stir to combine. Cook until dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat and set aside.

While the onion is cooking, combine the garlic, Italian herbs, plain flour and salt in a medium bowl. Add the chicken and toss to coat. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add 1/2 the chicken and cook, tossing regularly, until browned and cooked through, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel. Repeat with the remaining chicken, adding more oil if needed.

Combine the grated Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, water (for the dressing) and 2 tsp olive oil in a small bowl. TIP:  If you don’t like mustard, add a little at a time and taste as you go. Season with a pinch of pepper. Mix well and set aside. In a medium bowl, place the cos lettuce and 1 tbs of the Parmesan dressing. Toss to coat.

Heat the mini flour tortillas in a sandwich press, or on a plate in the microwave for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

Divide the dressed cos lettuce, tomato and carrot between tortillas. Top with the chicken and caramelised onion. Spoon over the remaining Parmesan dressing.